        "title": "fix(agents): keep lightweight cron prompts out of no-op compaction",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes #96658.\n\nLightweight isolated cron runs on very small context windows can reserve too much of the model window for response headroom before the first prompt is sent. In the reported 4,096-token model case, current `main` leaves only 2,048 prompt tokens for a 3,544-token lightweight cron prompt, so the precheck routes to `compact_only` even though lightweight cron has no bootstrap history to compact.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThis keeps the shared small-context prompt floor conservative: `MIN_PROMPT_BUDGET_RATIO` remains `0.5` for full-context callers, settings reserve capping, CLI compaction, mid-turn guard paths, and lightweight shared-history runs such as non-isolated heartbeats.\n\nThe higher 87.5% prompt share is now scoped to history-free lightweight pre-prompt admission only. The precheck also subtracts estimated tool-schema pressure before accepting `fits`, using the provider-visible tool surface from both runtime tools and client-supplied tool definitions.\n\n`toolSchemaTokens` is diagnostic-only and optional on `PreemptiveCompactionDecision`, preserving the public `openclaw/plugin-sdk/agent-harness-runtime` type shape for existing SDK consumers.\n\n## User Impact\n\nLightweight cron jobs on small-context fallback models can proceed when the rendered prompt plus tool schema surface fits the model window, instead of failing through repeated compact-only recovery with nothing useful to compact.\n\nTool-heavy small-context runs and shared-history lightweight runs remain conservative, and non-lightweight/full-context paths keep the previous shared reserve behavior.\n\n## Evidence\n\nEarlier real lightweight cron behavior proof on this PR branch:\n\n```text\nSetup: source Gateway from this PR branch, temp HOME and OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR, local mock OpenAI Responses server.\nConfig: openai/gpt-5.5 contextWindow=4096 contextTokens=4096, agents.defaults.compaction.reserveTokens=20000.\nAction: cron.add with sessionTarget=isolated, payload.kind=agentTurn, payload.lightContext=true, then cron.run mode=force.\nResult: cron finished status=ok; mock provider received 2 POST /v1/responses requests.\n```\n\nGateway debug proof from that run:\n\n```text\n[context-overflow-precheck] pre-prompt check ... provider=openai/gpt-5.5 route=fits estimatedPromptTokens=3318 pressureSource=llm_boundary_normalized_prompt promptBudgetBeforeReserve=3584 overflowTokens=0 toolResultReducibleChars=0 reserveTokens=20000 effectiveReserveTokens=512 contextTokenBudget=4096 messages=0 unwindowedMessages=0 sessionFile=<tmp-state>/agents/main/sessions/<session>.jsonl\n```\n\nCurrent-head boundary proof for the reported 4,096-token / 20,000-reserve / 3,544-token case:\n\n```text\nhistory-free lightweight, no tools: route=fits, promptBudgetBeforeReserve=3584, toolSchemaTokens=0, effectiveReserveTokens=512\nhistory-free lightweight, 570-token schema: route=compact_only, promptBudgetBeforeReserve=3014, overflowTokens=530\nlightweight with shared history: route=compact_only, promptBudgetBeforeReserve=2048\nfull mode, no tools: route=compact_only, promptBudgetBeforeReserve=2048\n```\n\nRed test before the original fix:\n\n```text\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/preemptive-compaction.test.ts\nAssertionError: expected 2048 to be greater than or equal to 3544\n```\n\nFocused validation on current head `26ea90c853a`:\n\n```text\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/preemptive-compaction.test.ts src/agents/command/cli-compaction.test.ts\n# PASS 39 tests\n\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugin-sdk/agent-harness-runtime.test.ts\n# PASS 16 tests\n\nnode scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.core.test.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/core-test.tsbuildinfo\n# PASS\n\nnode_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/preemptive-compaction.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/preemptive-compaction.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.ts src/plugin-sdk/agent-harness-runtime.test.ts src/agents/command/cli-compaction.test.ts\n# PASS\n\ngit diff --check\n# PASS\n```\n\nReview comments addressed:\n\n- Codex's original tool-schema budgeting concern: addressed by subtracting tool schema pressure before history-free lightweight `fits` admission.\n- Codex's client-supplied tools follow-up: addressed by budgeting `effectiveTools` plus `clientToolDefs`, matching the provider-visible custom tool surface used for the session.\n- Codex's heartbeat/shared-history follow-up: addressed by keeping lightweight runs with any history on the shared 2,048-token floor for 4k models.\n- ClawSweeper's SDK compatibility finding: addressed by making `toolSchemaTokens` optional and adding a plugin SDK type compatibility test that constructs the old decision shape.\n\nAutoreview: attempted one local draft-PR review round, but the helper failed before review due local Codex config parsing (`service_tier = priority`; helper expected `fast` or `flex`). No review findings were produced.\n\nAgent transcript: a matching local session was found, but no transcript is included because adding sanitized transcript logs requires explicit approval.\n\n",
