        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes #96658.\n\nLightweight isolated cron runs on very small context windows can reserve too much of the model window for response headroom before the first prompt is sent. In the reported 4,096-token model case, current `main` leaves only 2,048 prompt tokens for a 3,544-token lightweight cron prompt, so the precheck routes to `compact_only` even though lightweight cron has no bootstrap history to compact.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThis keeps the shared small-context prompt floor conservative: `MIN_PROMPT_BUDGET_RATIO` remains `0.5` for full-context callers, settings reserve capping, CLI compaction, mid-turn guard paths, and lightweight shared-history runs such as non-isolated heartbeats.\n\nThe higher 87.5% prompt share is now scoped to history-free lightweight pre-prompt admission only. The precheck also subtracts estimated tool-schema pressure before accepting `fits`, using the provider-visible tool surface from both runtime tools and client-supplied tool definitions.\n\n`toolSchemaTokens` is diagnostic-only and optional on `PreemptiveCompactionDecision`, preserving the public `openclaw/plugin-sdk/agent-harness-runtime` type shape for existing SDK consumers.\n\n## User Impact\n\nLightweight cron jobs on small-context fallback models can proceed when the rendered prompt plus tool schema surface fits the model window, instead of failing through repeated compact-only recovery with nothing useful to compact.\n\nTool-heavy small-context runs and shared-history lightweight runs remain conservative, and non-lightweight/full-context paths keep the previous shared reserve behavior.\n\n## Evidence\n\nEarlier real lightweight cron behavior proof on this PR branch:\n\n```text\nSetup: source Gateway from this PR branch, temp HOME and OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR, local mock OpenAI Responses server.\nConfig: openai/gpt-5.5 contextWindow=4096 contextTokens=4096, agents.defaults.compaction.reserveTokens=20000.\nAction: cron.add with